<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-244] RewriteAppender ignores the filter that&apos;s passed to it.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-244</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The RewriteAppender ignores the filter provided. It just passes null instead of adding the filter.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It occurs on the line where the AppenderControl is added to the ConcurrentMap.  Instead of passing null, it could just pass the reference to the filter that it already passes to the super class.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
